data.title: Woody Allen Film Casts Elle Fanning, Timothée Chalamet and More
data.meta_description: Woody Allen has announced the cast members of his upcoming as-yet-untitled film, which include Elle Fanning, Timothée Chalamet and Selena Gomez.
data.meta_site_name: ComingSoon.net - Movie Trailers, TV & Streaming News, and More
data.text:
Woody Allen has revealed new cast members for his untitled film including Timothée Chalamet and Elle Fanning

Woody Allen has revealed the cast of his upcoming untitled feature film. The cast includes Timothée Chalamet (Call Me By Your Name, Interstellar), Elle Fanning (The Beguiled, The Neon Demon), and Selena Gomez (Spring Breakers, Hotel Transylvania). The film has secured theatrical distribution through Amazon Studios.

Allen has collaborated with Amazon Studios before with Cafe Society and Crisis in Six Scenes. Amazon will release his latest completed film Wonder Wheel, starring James Belushi, Juno Temple, Justin Timberlake, and Kate Winslet, in select markets on December 1. A national theatrical expansion will follow and the film will be available exclusively to Amazon Prime members after its run. Wonder Wheel is set in Coney Island during the 1950s.

Elle Fanning is known for her work in the J.J. Abrams drama Super 8. She’s also been seen in films like Phoebe in Wonderland, Somewhere, We Bought a Zoo, Ginger and Rosa, Maleficent with Angelina Jolie and The Neon Demon. She also played Daisy at age 7 in The Curious Case of Benjamin Button.

Timothée Chalamet is known for his work as the young Tom in Interstellar and appeared in the TV series Homeland as Tim Walden. He played Luke in the series Royal Pains. Chalamet has also been seen in Love the Coopers, The Adderall Diaries, Call Me By Your Name and Hot Summer Nights. He’ll be seen next in Hostiles with Christian Bale and Rosamund Pike.

Selena Gomez hit the scene in the Disney Channel show The Wizards of Waverly Place. She translated her fame into a successful music career, though she continued acting. Gomez was the voice of Mavis in the Hotel Transylvania movies and played Faith in Spring Breakers.

What do you guys think of the casting of Elle Fanning, Timothée Chalamet and Selena Gomez in the upcoming Woody Allen film? Let us know your thoughts in the comments or tweet them to us @ComingSoonnet.
